1 'CIS PROLINE - PRO      75' 
2 
;SITE AS1 (GLU 78, CYS 172) REFERS TO THE CATALYTIC ACIDIC RESIDUES.  IN THE NATIVE SEQUENCE THEY ARE GLU 78 AND GLU 172.  SITE AS2 (TYR 5, TYR 69, TYR 80, TYR 166) REFERS TO THE GROUP OF TYROSINE RESIDUES IN THE ACTIVE SITE THAT APPEAR TO BE IMPORTANT FOR SUBSTRATE BINDING.
;
3 
;ALL NON-GLYCINE RESIDUES LIE WITHIN THE ALLOWED REGIONS OF THE RAMACHANDRAN PLOT EXCEPT ASP 121 AND ALA 165.  THE ELECTRON DENSITY FOR BOTH ASP 121 AND ALA 165 IS VERY CLEAR.
;
